cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on finding heavy hitters in network measurement. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes an improvement to the Elastic sketch algorithm. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possibility as finding heavy hitters can be useful in detecting network attacks. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as heavy hitters can be used to identify popular content or users in social networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility as the paper discusses the error rate and speed of the proposed algorithm.
